Class LocatableConfigurationBase<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intellij.openapi.util.UserDataHolderBase
      • com.intellij.execution.configurations.RunConfigurationBase<T>
        • com.intellij.execution.configurations.LocatableConfigurationBase<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ConfigurationCreationListener, LocatableConfiguration, RunConfiguration, RunProfile, TargetAwareRunProfile, UserDataHolder, UserDataHolderEx, java.lang.Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AntRunConfiguration, ExternalSystemRunConfiguration, JarApplicationConfiguration, ModuleBasedConfiguration, RemoteDebugConfiguration, RuntimeConfiguration, RuntimeConfigurationProducer.DelegatingRuntimeConfiguration, ShRunConfiguration, XsltRunConfiguration

    public abstract class LocatableConfigurationBase<T>
extends RunConfigurationBase<T>
implements LocatableConfiguration
    Common base class that should be used for configurations that can be created from context by a RunConfigurationProducer}. It supports automatically generating a name for a configuration from its settings and keeping track of whether the name was changed by the user.

      • getActionName

        public java.lang.String getActionName()
        Returns the text of the context menu action to start this run configuration. This can be different from the run configuration name (for example, for a Java unit test method, the context menu shows just the name of the method, whereas the name of the run configuration includes the class name).
        Returns:
        the name of the action.
